@startuml widget-recovery-session-replacement
title Widget Recovery and Session Replacement

hide footbox

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontColor #111111
  ParticipantFontSize 16
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorFontSize 16
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

actor "Visitor" as Visitor
participant "Widget UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Recovery\nController" as Controller
participant "Recovery\nService" as RecoveryService
participant "OTP + Email" as OtpEmail
participant "Domain Models\nWidget/Recovery/Session/Contact/Ticket" as Models
participant "WidgetPublic\nService" as PublicService
participant "Realtime\nRuntime" as Realtime

== 1. Request recovery ==

Visitor -> UI: Enters recovery email
UI -> Routes: POST recovery/request
Routes -> Controller: validated email request
Controller -> RecoveryService: requestWidgetRecovery(publicKey, email)
RecoveryService -> Models: verify active widget/mailbox\nand find recoverable contact/ticket
RecoveryService -> OtpEmail: create widgetRecovery OTP\nand send email when candidate exists
RecoveryService --> UI: generic recoveryRequested response

== 2. Verify OTP ==

Visitor -> UI: Enters OTP code
UI -> Routes: POST recovery/verify
Routes -> Controller: validated email + code
Controller -> RecoveryService: verifyWidgetRecovery(publicKey, email, code)
RecoveryService -> OtpEmail: verify widget-scoped OTP
RecoveryService -> Models: reload recovery candidate\nand create wgr_* recovery record
RecoveryService --> UI: recovery token + candidate options

== 3. Continue or start new ==

Visitor -> UI: Chooses recovery action

alt Continue recovered conversation
  UI -> Routes: POST recovery/continue
  Routes -> Controller: validated recoveryToken
  Controller -> RecoveryService: continueRecoveredWidgetConversation(wgr_*)
  RecoveryService -> Models: load valid recovery record\nand recoverable ticket
  RecoveryService -> Models: ensure verified contact/identity
  RecoveryService -> PublicService: create fresh wgs_* session\nbound to candidate ticket
else Start new conversation
  UI -> Routes: POST recovery/start-new
  Routes -> Controller: validated recoveryToken
  Controller -> RecoveryService: startNewRecoveredWidgetConversation(wgr_*)
  RecoveryService -> Models: load valid recovery record
  RecoveryService -> Models: ensure verified contact/identity
  RecoveryService -> PublicService: create fresh wgs_* session\nwithout ticket binding
end

== 4. Replace session ==

RecoveryService -> Models: invalidate superseded widget sessions\nand clear old publicSessionKeyHash
RecoveryService -> Realtime: disconnect replaced widget sockets
RecoveryService -> Models: consume recovery record

== 5. Return recovered session ==

RecoveryService -> PublicService: initializePublicWidgetSession(new wgs_*)
PublicService -> Models: load recovered session snapshot
PublicService --> UI: recovered session + conversation + realtime metadata

@enduml
